{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, we use the 4XMM-DR12 catalogue for a consistency check of our eRASS1 sources.We selected 1250.8k point sources from the eRASS1 1B catalogue and 432.9k point sources (SC_SUM_FLAG=0 and SC_EXTENT=0) from 4XMM-DR12 over the entire sky, and performed a simple positional cross-correlation between them, adopting a maximum separation of 10 ′′.",
    "We found 16.5k detection pairs.",
    "The majority of the X-ray sources are in the low S/N regime, where their fluxes suffer large uncertainties and Eddington bias.",
    "Taking the ratio of 0.2-2 keV flux to flux uncertainty as a measurement of flux measurement reliability, we selected sources with at least 1σ reliability in both catalogues and compared their fluxes in the upper panel of Fig. 13.",
    "For faint sources, the Eddington bias is still visible in terms of the overestimated A34, page 19 of 38 eROSITA fluxes at the low-flux end."
  ]
}